com.simplewebframework.webelements

Class HtmlElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.simplewebframework.webelements.HtmlElement
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ButtonElement, CheckBoxElement, ImageElement, LabelElement, LinkElement, RadioButtonElement, SelectList, Table, TextFieldElement

    public class HtmlElement
extends Object
    Provides methods to interact with a web page. All HTML element (ButtonElement, LinkElement, TextFieldElement, etc.) extends from this class.

      • findElement

        protected void findElement()
        Finds the element using By type. Implicit Waits is built in createWebDriver() in WebUIDriver to handle dynamic element problem. This method is invoked before all the basic operations like click, sendKeys, getText, etc. Use waitForPresent to use Explicit Waits to deal with special element which needs long time to present.
